After spending 5 days in captivity, the Commissioner for National Population Commission in Bayelsa State, Gloria Izonfuo has regained freedom from her abductors. Gunmen had kidnapped the NPC Commissioner along Ogbakiri axis of the East-West Road in Rivers State last Sunday. Izonfuo was kidnapped alongside her driver and maid while returning from a trip to Brass, Bayelsa state. The spokesperson of the Rivers State Police Command, Grace Iringe-Koko has however confirmed her release.